$Packages$openssl$`Authors@R`
[1] "c(person(\"Jeroen\", \"Ooms\", role = c(\"aut\", \"cre\"), email = \"jeroenooms@gmail.com\", comment = c(ORCID = \"0000-0002-4035-0289\")), person(\"Oliver\", \"Keyes\", role = \"ctb\"))"

$Packages$openssl$Description
[1] "Bindings to OpenSSL libssl and libcrypto, plus custom SSH key parsers. Supports RSA, DSA and EC curves P-256, P-384, P-521, and curve25519. Cryptographic signatures can either be created and verified manually or via x509 certificates.  AES can be used in cbc, ctr or gcm mode for symmetric encryption; RSA for asymmetric (public key) encryption or EC for Diffie Hellman. High-level envelope functions  combine RSA and AES for encrypting arbitrary sized data. Other utilities include key generators, hash functions (md5, sha1, sha256, etc), base64 encoder, a secure random number generator, and 'bignum' math methods for manually performing crypto  calculations on large multibyte integers."

